The paper discusses recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The use of side information also suggests a potential overlap with the social and information networks (cs.SI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses different representations of side information, including text, image, and video features, which could fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) categories.
